Import the required libraries.
Create a JavaSampler class that extends the Selenium WebDriver class.
Create a JMeter test plan and add a SeleniumSampler to it.

Add a Thread Group to your test plan.

Right-click on the Thread Group and select Add > Sampler > Java Sampler.

In the Java Sampler properties dialog box, enter the following information:

Class name: SeleniumSampler
Arguments: Any arguments that you want to pass to the SeleniumSampler class, such as the URL of the web page to open and the ID of the button to click.
Click OK to add the SeleniumSampler to the test plan.

Add any other controllers that you want to use to control the SeleniumSampler, such as a Loop Controller or a Switch Controller.

Run the test plan.
